I think with the amount of capacity in the money market complex and the fact that the Fed increase their RRP facility, now that facility is at zero, so that certainly is supportive of ensuring short rates don't go negative for any meaningful period of time. They also obviously could increase that. And then for us, I would say, not a meaningful impact because obviously, we have 10 basis points of IOER as an option for us, but we do trade around it.

Jamie Dimon -- Chairman and Chief Executive Officer

